1.9.1 Chain of Thought (CoT) Visibility
To overcome the ""Black Box"" nature of AI, Yellow.ai exposes the ""Chain of Thought"" (CoT). Administrators can view a trace of the Orchestrator LLM's decision-making process: which user intent was detected, which tools were considered, why a specific tool was selected, and exactly which ""chunks"" of knowledge were retrieved from the vector database. This transparency is essential for debugging and compliance.   

1.9.2 Insights and Self-Healing
The ""Insights"" module provides real-time dashboards tracking standard KPIs (Deflection Rate, Goal Completion, CSAT). More importantly, the ""Analyze"" feature uses unsupervised learning to cluster uncategorized user queries, identifying emerging topics or ""Unknown Intents."" This feeds into a ""Self-Healing"" loop: the system suggests new Knowledge Base articles or flow modifications to address these gaps. The ""Smart Sync"" feature ensures that as underlying documents (e.g., a policy PDF on SharePoint) change, the bot’s index is automatically updated, preventing information drift.   
