1.13.1 Connect vs. Collect Strategy
Yellow.ai adheres to a ""Connect vs. Collect"" integration philosophy. It does not seek to become the system of record; rather, it orchestrates the existing systems. The platform supports standard integration protocols (REST, SOAP, GraphQL) and provides 150+ pre-built connectors for the enterprise stack (SAP, Oracle, Microsoft Dynamics, Salesforce).   

1.13.2 Handling Custom Backends
For highly customized legacy systems (e.g., a 20-year-old on-premise mainframe with a SOAP wrapper), the platform offers ""Custom API Nodes."" Developers can import the legacy system's definition files (WSDL, Swagger) to generate the connection. The ""Generative Integration"" tool further simplifies this by allowing developers to simply describe the API endpoint or paste a sample request, with the AI generating the necessary boilerplate code to bridge the modern agent with the legacy backend.   
