 During the customer experience demonstration please:
 
  * Include a voice interaction with a customer that highlights the vendor's approach to providing the highest quality voice interactions.
  * Explain the telephony connection made on this demo call, and any implications this will have on voice quality."	0	"Voice and Telephony Support
Voice is a standalone pillar of the Yellow.ai offering, branded as ""VoiceX."" This is not merely a text-bot connected to a speech-to-text engine; it is a dedicated voice orchestration stack.

1.14.1 VoiceX and Full-Duplex Architecture
The core differentiator of VoiceX is ""Full-Duplex"" capability. Traditional voice bots are ""Simplex"" (half-duplex)—they listen, then process, then speak. They cannot listen while speaking. VoiceX is Full-Duplex. It can process user input while simultaneously generating audio output. This enables ""Barge-In"" (interruption handling)—if a user says ""Stop, I got it,"" the bot stops instantly. It also enables ""Back-Channeling,"" where the bot can make affirmative sounds (""Uh-huh,"" ""I see"") while the user is talking, signaling active listening without interrupting the flow.   

1.14.2 Quality and Latency
VoiceX is engineered for ""Sub-Second Latency"" (<800ms), creating a conversational rhythm that mimics human telephony. It includes ""Sentiment-Adaptive Latency,"" dynamically adjusting the speed and pitch of the voice based on the user's emotion. If a user is detected as ""Angry"" or ""Frustrated,"" the bot slows down and adopts a more empathetic, calm tone. The infrastructure supports SIP trunking and integrates with major telephony providers (Twilio, Genesys, Avaya), ensuring carrier-grade voice quality.   

"																					
